ctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003Elymphangitis\u003C/strong\u003E, which specifically refers to inflammation of lymphatic vessels. It typically appears as red streaks under the skin tracking along lymphatic channels, often from a site of infection towards regional lymph nodes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELymphadenitis\u003C/strong\u003E refers to inflammation of lymph nodes, whilst \u003Cstrong\u003Elymphoedema\u003C/strong\u003E is the accumulation of lymphatic fluid in tissues due to impaired lymphatic drainage. \u003Cstrong\u003ELymphadenopathy\u003C/strong\u003E is the enlargement of lymph nodes from any cause, and \u003Cstrong\u003Elymphoma\u003C/strong\u003E is a malignant neoplasm of lymphoid tissue.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Lymphangitis refers specifically to inflammation of lymphatic vessels, appearing as red streaks under the skin","Different lymphatic conditions have distinct terminology: lymphadenitis (node inflammation), lymphangitis (vessel inflammation), lymphoedema (fluid accumulation), lymphadenopathy (node enlargement), lymphoma (malignancy)"],"references":["Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Null M, Arbor TC, Agarwal M. Anatomy, Lymphatic System. 2023 Mar 6. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30020619.","Bona, C. A., \u0026 Bonilla, F. A. (2019). Textbook of immunology. CRC press"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97422"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14972"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97422","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97422"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-23T16:58:32+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-23T16:58:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"it